23 extension of not more than 6 months for good cause shown. A person who fails to
24 obtain this certification within the prescribed period of time is prohibited from
25 exercising the powers of a peace officer. (NRS 289.550) Section 1 mandates that an
26 employee of a federal agency who holds a position designated in an agreement
27 entered into pursuant to section 1 be certified by the Commission not later than 6
28 months after the date on which: (1) the written agreement became effective; or (2)
29 the person commences employment with the federal agency, if the person
30 commences employment after the date on which the written agreement became
31 effective. Section 3 of this bill exempts such federal employees from the time
32 frame in existing law for initial certification.
33 Existing law recognizes certain persons as peace officers. (NRS 289.150-
34 289.360) Section 2 of this bill confers the same powers of a peace officer on the
35 federal employees who hold positions designated in an agreement entered into
36 pursuant to section 1 when performing duties for the purposes, and within the
37 scope, of the written agreement.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 248 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. Each sheriff may enter into a written agreement with a
4 federal agency to authorize employees of the federal agency who
5 hold positions for which the primary responsibility is the
6 investigation and enforcement of federal laws to enforce state or
7 local laws, or both, within the jurisdiction and authority of the
8 sheriff.
9 2. Any written agreement entered into pursuant to
10 subsection 1:
11 (a) Must, without limitation:
12 (1) Be limited to a term of not more than 2 years.
13 (2) Designate the state or local laws, or both, to be
14 enforced.
15 (3) Designate each position with the federal agency to
16 which the written agreement applies.
17 (4) Prescribe the grounds for revocation of the authority of
18 an employee of the federal agency under the agreement.
19 (b) Must not grant any authority to an employee of the federal
20 agency that is outside of the jurisdiction and authority of the
21 sheriff.
22 3. An employee of a federal agency who holds a position with
23 the federal agency that is designated pursuant to subparagraph (3)
24 of paragraph (a) of subsection 2 in a written agreement entered
25 into pursuant to subsection 1 must be certified by the Peace
26 Officers’ Standards and Training Commission not later than 6
27 months after the date on which:
28 (a) The written agreement became effective; or
